name: Unidentified_Resolute_navigation_officer_(Battle_of_Ryloth)
display_name: Unidentified Resolute navigation officer (Battle of Ryloth)
content: A clone navigation officer served aboard the Resolute during the Clone Wars, participating in strategy planning for the Battle of Ryloth. After Jedi Padawan Ahsoka Tano led a disastrous assault on the Separatist blockade, Anakin Skywalker prepared a new strategy that involved him sacrificing their crippled Star Destroyer Defender, Tano suggested a method to help attack the remaining ships of the enemy blockade, proposing to turn the Resolute's hull to face the enemy and allow Republic bombers to do their damage once the enemy was drawn in. The officer was skeptical and suggested more planning, but given the urgency of the situation, command agreed to the plan.
